        <p>Data, Development, Infrastructure, Interoperability, Live Services SM, Security, Solution Assurance and Usability and Accessibility.</p>
        <p>They will look to gauge your awareness, alignment to policies and standards, consideration and engagement with each of these areas within your proposed programme/activity and may require further information.</p>
        <p>The CCC owner will review what is on the portal and will either approve, ignore (if it isnâ€™t relevant), reject or ask questions for clarification. It is your responsibility to respond to any CCC questions or concerns in a timely manner to ensure no delays at TRG.</p>
